{"questionId":"20354","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>A particle moves in a straight line. The velocity,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>v</mi><mo> </mo><msup><mtext>ms</mtext><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup></math>,&nbsp;of the particle at time <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>t</mi></math> seconds is&nbsp;given by <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>v</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>t</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>=</mo><mi>t</mi><mo> </mo><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><mi>t</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn></math>, for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>≤</mo><mi>t</mi><mo>≤</mo><mn>10</mn></math>.</p>\n<p>The following diagram shows the graph of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>v</mi></math>.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/1a9e54ea1fc1e6317183726636b07d7b823a0dd4.png\"></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Find the smallest value of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>t</mi></math> for which the particle is at rest.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p>recognising&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>v</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>t</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>6</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>74416</mn><mo>…</mo></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>6</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>74</mn></math>&nbsp;(sec)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Do not award <em><strong>A1</strong></em> if additional values are given.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"20354","referenceCode":"21M.2.SL.TZ1.5a","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Find the smallest value of t for which the particle is at rest.","paper":"2","level":"